<div class="dokuwiki export">

<p>
<strong>C++ fundamental (primitive) types:</strong>
</p>
<ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> bool</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> char</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> int</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> float</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> double</div>
</li>
</ul>

<p>
<em>Optionally:</em>
</p>
<ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> void </div>
</li>
</ul>

<p>

<strong>Additional qualifiers for the primitive types:</strong>
</p>
<ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> signed</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> unsigned</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> short</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> long</div>
</li>
</ul>

<p>

<strong>Using the two together:</strong>
</p>

<p>
<em class="u">bool</em>: 1 byte (Range: true or false)
</p>

<p>
signed char = <em class="u">char</em>: 1 byte, (Range: -128 to 127)
</p>

<p>
unsigned char: 1 byte (Range: 0 to 255)
</p>

<p>
short = short int = signed short int: 2 bytes (Range: -2^15 to 2^15-1)
</p>

<p>
unsigned short = unsigned short int: 2 bytes (Range: 0 to 2^16-1)
</p>

<p>
long = long int = signed long int = signed int = <em class="u">int</em>: 4 bytes (Range: -2^31 to 2^31-1)
</p>

<p>
usigned long = unsigned long int = unsigned int: 4 bytes (Range: 0 to 2^32-1)
</p>

<p>
<em class="u">float</em>: 4 bytes (Cannot be unsigned, short, long. Range: 3.4e-38 to 3.4e+38, 7 digits)
</p>

<p>
<em class="u">double</em>: 8 bytes (Cannot be unsigned, short. Range: 1.7e-308 to 1.7e+308, 15 digits)
</p>

<p>
long double: 10 bytes (Range:)

</p>
<hr />

<p>

